                        <interp source="ph_021" xml:id="ana_021"><!-- link -->
                            <desc>
                                The expression "draussen" ("out there") could refer either to <rs type="place" ref="#amp_place_id_7">Schloss Fridau</rs> or to <rs type="place" ref="#amp_place_id_74">Zell am See</rs>, where <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_167">Janko Musulin</rs> owned the guest house <rs type="place" ref="#amp_place_id_258">Fallegg</rs>, which was managed by <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_141">Sonja Lanier</rs> in the period circa 1957 to circa 1965. In an e-mail from 12 January 2024, <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_142">Amelie Lanier</rs> states that she has never been to Fridau.
